<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 18 at 1:20PM EST  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A line of snow showers will affect eastern Erie County Until 245
PM EST....
At 117 PM EST, radar indicated snow showers along a line extending
from Erie to near Garland, moving northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...Visibility dropping to less than a quarter mile. A
brief period of accumulating snow is expected with this band. Snow
accumulations around a half an inch, locally up to an inch, is
expected with this snow band. The snow band will continue to move
northeast during the afternoon hours.
Locations impacted include...
Erie, Corry, North East, Wattsburg, Northwest Harborcreek,
Harborcreek, Lawrence Park, Wesleyville, Elgin and Northwest
Harborcr.
Use extra caution if you must travel. Rapid changes in visibility and
potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.</description>
